      "content": "Dehydration can indeed cause dizziness and thirst, but it's crucial to approach this carefully. Drinking large amounts of water suddenly can lead to other issues. Instead, gradually increase your water intake throughout the day and ensure you're also eating balanced meals to help maintain your electrolyte levels. Always monitor the color of your urine—light yellow indicates proper hydration. If you're consistently feeling dizzy or any other symptoms persist, it would be wise to consult your doctor, who can check your lithium levels and ensure you're on the right dosage. Your health is paramount, and it's better to be safe than sorry.",
