      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While it's understandable to want to avoid unnecessary doctor's visits, it's also important to recognize when symptoms might indicate a need for professional intervention. Feeling dizzy and extra thirsty could be signs of dehydration or even lithium toxicity, especially when combined with other symptoms like shaking and nausea. Increasing water intake is good, but adding extra salt without medical advice can lead to an imbalance in electrolytes. Keeping track of your symptoms and seeking a doctor's advice might save you from potential complications. It's always better to err on the side of caution when it comes to your health.",
      "source": "target",
